[Southwest Georgia is a 14-county region in the U.S. state of Georgia. It has a 2010 census population of 496 433 and is the least populated region in Georgia, just slightly behind Southeast Georgia; additionally, the area has historically been the poorest region of the state since at least 1995, when over 25% of the residents were in poverty (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southwest_Georgia#Counties).

The city of Albany (population 77 434) is the most populous city and the region's sole metropolitan area. Southwest Georgia includes the following counties: Baker, Calhoun, Colquitt, Decatur, Dougherty, Early, Grady, Lee, Miller, Mitchell, Seminole, Terrell, Thomas, and Worth (http://www.southwestgeorgiapublichealth.org). A map showing the location of Southwest Georgia can be found at https://www.georgiastandards.org/Learning/Pages/ETC-RESA/RESA.aspx. - Mod.ML

