[4] USA (Utah)
Date: Thu 5 Apr 2018
Source: KSL [edited]
https://www.ksl.com/index.php?sid=46294465&nid=148&title=3-draper-schools-warn-parents-of-whooping-cough-outbreak


12 students have confirmed cases of whooping cough at 3 schools in Draper, officials said. Parents of Corner Canyon High School students were warned of an outbreak in late March [2018] after 5 students were diagnosed with the respiratory disease, according to Salt Lake County Health Department spokesman Nicholas Rupp. Corner Canyon is now reporting 7 cases, Draper Park Middle School reports 2 cases, and Oak Hollow Elementary reports 3.

Parents of Corner Canyon High School students were notified Thursday [5 Apr 2018] by the Salt Lake County Health Department of an outbreak of whooping cough at the school. The letter directs people with cold symptoms to contact their health care providers.

Out of 2200 students at Corner Canyon High, 105 students are exempt from vaccination either because of parental choice or medical conditions, according to Rupp. 21 of 1491 students at Draper Park Middle School and 35 of 658 students at Oak Hollow Elementary are also vaccine-exempted. "As a health department, we support parental choice. We just have to remind those parents who make this particular choice that the ramifications may be that their student is not able to attend school. For pertussis, it is 21 days after the last student confirmed case is no longer symptomatic," Rupp said. The health department's medical officer has not recommended that any unvaccinated students remain at home during the outbreak, according to Rupp. Those seeking immunization can contact their health provider or call the Salt Lake County Health Department at 385-468-7468.

[Byline: Liesl Nielsen]

